1
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:34,520
=Lady Liberty=

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 19=

3
00:02:10,470 --> 00:02:10,960
Miss Lin.

4
00:02:13,377 --> 00:02:14,111
Miss Lin?

5
00:02:19,750 --> 00:02:20,310
Mr. Cai.

6
00:02:21,520 --> 00:02:23,470
Well, the door's
been open the whole time.

7
00:02:25,630 --> 00:02:27,280
You don't look too well.

8
00:02:27,280 --> 00:02:27,800
What's wrong?

9
00:02:29,840 --> 00:02:30,400
I'm fine.

10
00:02:33,111 --> 00:02:34,222
You wanted to see me?

11
00:02:34,870 --> 00:02:36,560
I'm here for Zhangzhu.

12
00:02:39,430 --> 00:02:40,630
She's probably moved out.

13
00:02:42,870 --> 00:02:43,750
She contacted you?

14
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:46,750
She moved some stuff back,

15
00:02:46,822 --> 00:02:48,866
and she said she would
stay there for a while.

16
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:54,240
She ran into some issues at work.

17
00:02:55,133 --> 00:02:57,000
I told her verbally she was dismissed,

18
00:02:58,430 --> 00:03:00,400
but that's not really what I intended.

19
00:03:02,190 --> 00:03:03,910
She's actually quite
suitable for this job.

20
00:03:04,755 --> 00:03:05,977
That's not really a problem.

21
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:07,430
If she wants to find another job,

22
00:03:07,430 --> 00:03:08,360
I can still help her.

23
00:03:09,590 --> 00:03:10,430
It's just...

24
00:03:11,240 --> 00:03:11,590
I...

25
00:03:12,430 --> 00:03:13,630
Did you need something from me?

26
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:18,870
Yes,

27
00:03:19,960 --> 00:03:20,710
well,

28
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:22,711
I was worried Zhangzhu might have

29
00:03:22,733 --> 00:03:24,888
had an unpleasant
conflict with you at work,

30
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:27,977
and then the relationship
between our families

31
00:03:28,066 --> 00:03:29,600
would just come to an end.

32
00:03:30,030 --> 00:03:31,120
I think we should

33
00:03:31,240 --> 00:03:33,000
stay in touch as usual.

34
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:35,150
There are some things,

35
00:03:35,840 --> 00:03:37,560
like matters related to the house

36
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:38,800
or renovations,

37
00:03:39,150 --> 00:03:40,280
I can still help with those,

38
00:03:41,080 --> 00:03:41,470
right?

39
00:03:41,590 --> 00:03:43,066
See, we're already back in touch.

40
00:03:43,710 --> 00:03:44,710
Thank you, Mr. Cai.

41
00:03:46,630 --> 00:03:47,190
From now on,

42
00:03:47,280 --> 00:03:49,840
if there are any issues
related to the house,

43
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:51,960
I'll contact you.

44
00:03:53,310 --> 00:03:53,680
Alright.

45
00:03:56,288 --> 00:03:57,000
By the way,

46
00:03:57,430 --> 00:03:59,710
I brought a few
real estate project brochures.

47
00:03:59,710 --> 00:04:01,733
You can look through them
when you're feeling bothered.

48
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:03,710
I think,

49
00:04:03,870 --> 00:04:05,680
sometimes, changing your environment

50
00:04:06,430 --> 00:04:07,280
isn't a bad thing.

51
00:04:07,910 --> 00:04:09,000
Sometimes,

52
00:04:09,080 --> 00:04:10,400
external changes

53
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:12,310
can help bring about internal change.

54
00:04:14,590 --> 00:04:15,030
Thank you.

55
00:04:21,830 --> 00:04:23,430
I'm just worried Zhangzhu right now

56
00:04:24,355 --> 00:04:26,822
might not be in a good state,
mentally or emotionally.

57
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:28,680
If anything comes up,

58
00:04:28,830 --> 00:04:29,830
you can call me.

59
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:32,750
I only meant to scare her a little,

60
00:04:33,390 --> 00:04:34,430
so she'd learn her lesson.

61
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:38,560
Without her as my assistant right now,

62
00:04:39,511 --> 00:04:40,888
I can't manage either.

63
00:04:46,444 --> 00:04:48,244
I'll call her and ask her to come back.

64
00:04:50,630 --> 00:04:50,950
Alright.

65
00:04:51,510 --> 00:04:52,240
Then,

66
00:04:53,040 --> 00:04:53,720
I'll leave first.

67
00:04:55,430 --> 00:04:57,000
I brought some gifts.

68
00:04:57,310 --> 00:04:59,240
You can share them

69
00:04:59,888 --> 00:05:01,111
with the elders at home.

70
00:05:01,750 --> 00:05:02,270
And

71
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:04,390
if you're feeling upset, give me a call.

72
00:05:04,533 --> 00:05:06,177
I'll go look at properties with you.

73
00:05:06,222 --> 00:05:07,866
Whether you buy or not isn't important.

74
00:05:07,911 --> 00:05:09,200
The main thing is to relax a bit.

75
00:05:09,430 --> 00:05:10,510
Alright? I'll go with you.

76
00:05:11,070 --> 00:05:11,560
Thank you.

77
00:05:12,950 --> 00:05:13,310
Then...

78
00:05:14,390 --> 00:05:15,310
Then I'll head off now.

79
00:05:31,160 --> 00:05:31,630
Mantou,

80
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:34,360
call Zhangzhu and tell her

81
00:05:34,480 --> 00:05:36,600
to prepare tomorrow
morning's project meeting agenda.

82
00:05:38,510 --> 00:05:38,830
Yes.

83
00:05:41,510 --> 00:05:42,070
Also,

84
00:05:42,430 --> 00:05:45,360
call Fragile and ask how the contract
is going on Mr. Fan's side.

85
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:48,155
Why hasn't there been any follow-up
after it was sent?

86
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:50,560
Alright.

87
00:06:04,040 --> 00:06:04,360
Hello?

88
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:11,870
How is he now?

89
00:06:12,088 --> 00:06:13,800
Has he been taken to the hospital?

90
00:06:16,088 --> 00:06:17,155
I'll be there right away.

91
00:06:44,940 --> 00:06:47,820
(Zhanqiao)

92
00:06:54,940 --> 00:07:01,580
(Shanghai, Emergency)

93
00:07:37,500 --> 00:07:41,220
(Occupied)

94
00:07:50,222 --> 00:07:51,466
Prepare for defibrillation.

95
00:07:53,630 --> 00:07:55,800
Unsynchronized defibrillation,
200 joules.

96
00:07:55,911 --> 00:07:57,900
All non-essential personnel,
step away from the bed.

97
00:08:00,911 --> 00:08:02,670
The patient's heartbeat
has not returned.

98
00:08:02,680 --> 00:08:04,120
1 mg of epinephrine, IV push.

99
00:08:04,630 --> 00:08:06,360
1 mg of epinephrine, IV push.

100
00:08:06,400 --> 00:08:07,820
The patient's blood pressure is low.

101
00:08:07,830 --> 00:08:09,360
80 mg of dopamine, IV infusion.

102
00:08:16,866 --> 00:08:18,800
The patient's heartbeat
still hasn't returned.

103
00:08:18,820 --> 00:08:19,740
Second defibrillation.

104
00:08:19,750 --> 00:08:22,070
Unsynchronized defibrillation,
200 joules.

105
00:08:22,377 --> 00:08:24,466
All non-essential personnel,
step away from the bed.

106
00:08:26,355 --> 00:08:27,990
No history of allergies.
No surgical history.

107
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:29,000
Blood oxygen is normal.

108
00:08:34,030 --> 00:08:35,360
1 mg of epinephrine, IV push.

109
00:08:36,320 --> 00:08:37,870
1 mg of epinephrine, IV push.

110
00:08:37,888 --> 00:08:38,688
Injection complete.

111
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:43,688
The patient's spontaneous
heartbeat has returned.

112
00:08:44,022 --> 00:08:45,355
Breathing has resumed.

113
00:09:03,720 --> 00:09:04,390
Awake?

114
00:09:05,550 --> 00:09:06,600
You recognize me, right?

115
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:10,030
I only had a little to drink.

116
00:09:10,066 --> 00:09:11,400
It's not that serious, right?

117
00:09:11,870 --> 00:09:13,270
That was just a little?

118
00:09:14,550 --> 00:09:15,630
Lately,

119
00:09:15,630 --> 00:09:17,790
do you remember what chapter
your latest update is on?

120
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:22,670
Love-Obsessed Husband?

121
00:09:23,644 --> 00:09:25,200
Didn't I already finish updating it?

122
00:09:27,670 --> 00:09:29,240
Still talking nonsense.

123
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:30,550
That means your brain's fine.

124
00:09:35,480 --> 00:09:36,440
Still not convinced?

125
00:09:37,022 --> 00:09:38,910
Do you want me
to get up and write a few lines

126
00:09:38,910 --> 00:09:39,720
to prove it?

127
00:09:41,240 --> 00:09:42,840
Can you really sit up?

128
00:09:45,022 --> 00:09:46,320
You actually want me to write?

129
00:09:47,910 --> 00:09:49,270
If you really can,

130
00:09:49,360 --> 00:09:50,720
go check on your dad.

131
00:09:55,840 --> 00:09:56,790
What happened to him?

132
00:09:57,670 --> 00:09:59,030
Lin Zhanqiao asked me to tell you

133
00:09:59,030 --> 00:10:01,755
that your dad drank some low-quality
alcohol from who knows where.

134
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:05,150
He's in the hospital now,
being resuscitated.

135
00:10:08,750 --> 00:10:09,440
Ignore him.

136
00:10:10,177 --> 00:10:12,150
It's not the first time
he's tried to kill himself.

137
00:10:12,160 --> 00:10:13,250
Isn't that the same for you?

138
00:10:13,270 --> 00:10:14,440
I don't have liver cancer.

139
00:10:28,088 --> 00:10:29,622
- Slow down.
- Where's the phone?

140
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:31,150
Sit still.

141
00:10:48,600 --> 00:10:49,320
What's going on?

142
00:10:50,422 --> 00:10:51,666
I'm at the hospital,

143
00:10:51,960 --> 00:10:52,750
next to your dad.

144
00:10:54,333 --> 00:10:55,630
How are things on your end?

145
00:10:57,150 --> 00:10:57,630
Hold on.

146
00:10:57,844 --> 00:10:59,120
Your dad wants to talk to you.

147
00:11:01,270 --> 00:11:01,790
It's He Han.

148
00:11:02,510 --> 00:11:03,200
I...

149
00:11:04,120 --> 00:11:05,120
don't want

150
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:07,750
to see him.

151
00:11:15,360 --> 00:11:16,240
Hurry over.

152
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:30,120
Is your dad okay?

153
00:11:41,150 --> 00:11:41,750
Slow down.

154
00:11:42,750 --> 00:11:44,066
Here, your clothes. Take them.

155
00:11:45,360 --> 00:11:45,870
Your bag...

156
00:11:46,510 --> 00:11:47,030
Take it slow.

157
00:12:01,240 --> 00:12:03,000
He Han is already on his way.

158
00:12:03,960 --> 00:12:04,960
No.

159
00:12:05,790 --> 00:12:07,120
No need.

160
00:12:11,960 --> 00:12:13,000
I've realized

161
00:12:14,510 --> 00:12:16,270
you and your son are actually the same.

162
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:18,440
You came to Shanghai to drink

163
00:12:18,910 --> 00:12:19,630
and eat with me.

164
00:12:21,150 --> 00:12:23,550
Was it really just about
drinking and eating with me?

165
00:12:27,440 --> 00:12:29,030
You just wanted to use me

166
00:12:30,670 --> 00:12:32,120
to hear news about He Han,

167
00:12:33,600 --> 00:12:35,600
to find out how he's been lately,

168
00:12:36,510 --> 00:12:37,000
right?

169
00:12:39,720 --> 00:12:40,550
He's the same.

170
00:12:41,910 --> 00:12:43,630
Every time I tell him about you,

171
00:12:44,630 --> 00:12:46,240
no matter what he says,

172
00:12:49,870 --> 00:12:51,630
he always listens patiently

173
00:12:52,630 --> 00:12:54,270
until I finish everything I have to say.

174
00:12:56,510 --> 00:12:57,120
Go...

175
00:12:57,840 --> 00:12:58,480
Go...

176
00:12:59,270 --> 00:12:59,670
Go...

177
00:13:16,390 --> 00:13:17,720
So, where is she now?

178
00:13:18,630 --> 00:13:19,960
Did you see her again after that?

179
00:13:24,911 --> 00:13:26,480
Family members, please step aside.

180
00:13:26,480 --> 00:13:27,933
We need to run an examination.

181
00:13:52,720 --> 00:13:53,510
How much longer?

182
00:13:55,440 --> 00:13:56,720
If traffic is normal,

183
00:13:56,910 --> 00:13:58,600
it'll take about an hour and a half.

184
00:14:49,511 --> 00:14:51,150
The patient's condition is very serious.

185
00:14:51,360 --> 00:14:52,550
You should

186
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:53,870
prepare yourselves.

187
00:14:54,240 --> 00:14:54,790
Doctor,

188
00:14:55,510 --> 00:14:56,910
is there any chance he can still...

189
00:14:57,511 --> 00:14:59,190
For patients with
late-stage liver cancer,

190
00:14:59,200 --> 00:15:01,150
their physical condition
is already unstable.

191
00:15:01,240 --> 00:15:03,320
On top of that,
he refused treatment and medication

192
00:15:03,440 --> 00:15:04,550
and even continued drinking.

193
00:15:04,622 --> 00:15:07,111
In his case, we really have already...

194
00:15:07,120 --> 00:15:08,830
Dr. Zhang, He Wei
has gone into cardiac arrest.

195
00:15:08,844 --> 00:15:09,900
He needs resuscitation again.

196
00:15:09,910 --> 00:15:10,390
Okay.

197
00:15:12,200 --> 00:15:12,600
Doctor,

198
00:15:13,600 --> 00:15:14,870
his son is already on the way.

199
00:15:14,870 --> 00:15:16,960
No matter what, please help him hold on.

200
00:15:17,044 --> 00:15:18,200
Alright, we'll do our best.

201
00:15:29,180 --> 00:15:31,500
(Emergency)

202
00:15:40,400 --> 00:15:41,555
You're not getting out?

203
00:15:47,177 --> 00:15:49,000
He said he doesn't want to see me.

204
00:15:50,177 --> 00:15:51,888
I don't want to see him either.

205
00:15:54,440 --> 00:15:56,240
Why are you like this?

206
00:15:57,311 --> 00:15:59,288
Well, if I see him,
what am I supposed to say?

207
00:15:59,630 --> 00:16:00,670
If he tells me to get lost,

208
00:16:01,510 --> 00:16:02,510
should I leave or stay?

209
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:05,480
He's old...

210
00:16:06,080 --> 00:16:07,150
He's old, so just

211
00:16:07,360 --> 00:16:08,510
take a step back first.

212
00:16:08,630 --> 00:16:09,550
So what if he's old?

213
00:16:11,044 --> 00:16:13,800
Does being old mean he doesn't
have to admit his mistakes or change?

214
00:16:14,270 --> 00:16:15,600
He's always been like this.

215
00:16:16,200 --> 00:16:17,150
Even before I was born,

216
00:16:17,150 --> 00:16:18,320
he was already a jerk.

217
00:16:20,320 --> 00:16:22,120
Maybe my problems were caused by him,

218
00:16:22,510 --> 00:16:24,200
but his problems weren't caused by me.

219
00:16:29,720 --> 00:16:31,840
Maybe if it weren't like this,

220
00:16:32,910 --> 00:16:35,790
you wouldn't have become
such a legendary online fiction writer,

221
00:16:36,800 --> 00:16:38,870
and you wouldn't have
made so much money, right?

222
00:16:38,870 --> 00:16:40,666
Do you really think I care about that?

223
00:16:46,377 --> 00:16:47,550
If that drinking last night

224
00:16:47,550 --> 00:16:49,155
had taken us both out, that'd be nice.

225
00:16:50,044 --> 00:16:51,644
It would've ended everything.

226
00:17:20,900 --> 00:17:23,380
(Zhanqiao)

227
00:17:36,511 --> 00:17:37,977
We've done everything we could.

228
00:17:38,066 --> 00:17:39,466
Please accept our condolences.

229
00:19:22,880 --> 00:19:24,000
Han, look.

230
00:19:24,733 --> 00:19:26,977
(Year 1992)
Isn't the Huangpu River magnificent?

231
00:19:27,750 --> 00:19:29,240
This is the Nanpu Bridge.

232
00:19:29,830 --> 00:19:33,480
It's the first bridge
spanning the Huangpu River.

233
00:19:36,300 --> 00:19:39,460
(Year 1997)

234
00:19:44,880 --> 00:19:46,030
Dad, look.

235
00:19:47,355 --> 00:19:49,177
(Award certificate)
Not bad, my son.

236
00:19:49,720 --> 00:19:50,640
You've got promise.

237
00:19:52,070 --> 00:19:54,480
You're already better
than I was at your age.

238
00:19:55,160 --> 00:19:55,830
That's great.

239
00:19:57,020 --> 00:20:00,500
(Year 2005)

240
00:20:24,060 --> 00:20:27,820
(Yutong Coach)

241
00:21:00,160 --> 00:21:01,800
You said you didn't want to see me,

242
00:21:04,030 --> 00:21:05,030
but I still had to come.

243
00:21:13,866 --> 00:21:16,044
From now on,
we can both finally be at peace.

244
00:21:21,400 --> 00:21:23,350
We won't have to live
with gritted teeth anymore.

245
00:22:22,030 --> 00:22:23,110
I've been here for a while.

246
00:22:23,480 --> 00:22:26,510
I... I don't know if he wants to see me.

247
00:22:30,070 --> 00:22:31,510
I was wrong again.

248
00:22:31,510 --> 00:22:33,110
Lin Zhanqiao, I was wrong again.

249
00:22:33,110 --> 00:22:34,240
I was wrong again.

250
00:22:35,550 --> 00:22:36,160
I...

251
00:22:39,110 --> 00:22:40,590
I don't know...

252
00:24:20,733 --> 00:24:21,888
It's alright now.

253
00:24:22,822 --> 00:24:24,533
You should head back and get some rest.

254
00:24:24,555 --> 00:24:26,000
You haven't slept all night.

255
00:24:31,750 --> 00:24:33,000
Really, don't worry, I...

256
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:46,440
He asked me to tell you

257
00:24:48,510 --> 00:24:49,350
he lied to you.

258
00:24:51,480 --> 00:24:52,720
Your mother didn't die.

259
00:24:54,000 --> 00:24:54,880
She left.

260
00:24:56,911 --> 00:24:58,111
She couldn't stand him,

261
00:24:58,750 --> 00:24:59,590
so she left.

262
00:25:01,640 --> 00:25:02,920
He felt sorry for you.

263
00:25:33,440 --> 00:25:34,030
You are...

264
00:25:34,030 --> 00:25:35,070
You're Miss Lin, right?

265
00:25:35,310 --> 00:25:36,550
I'm your mother's caregiver.

266
00:25:36,822 --> 00:25:37,480
Where's my mom?

267
00:25:37,510 --> 00:25:38,350
She's inside.

268
00:25:40,030 --> 00:25:40,440
Thank you.

269
00:25:43,200 --> 00:25:43,640
Mom.

270
00:25:46,311 --> 00:25:47,866
Mom, what happened to you?

271
00:25:48,160 --> 00:25:49,070
I fell.

272
00:25:49,310 --> 00:25:50,310
I hurt my back.

273
00:25:52,000 --> 00:25:53,920
Something this serious.
Why didn't you tell me?

274
00:25:55,400 --> 00:25:56,750
Your dad wouldn't let me tell you.

275
00:25:56,880 --> 00:25:58,977
He said he was afraid
it would affect your work.

276
00:25:59,030 --> 00:26:00,444
Why wouldn't he let you tell me?

277
00:26:00,920 --> 00:26:02,480
You can't move or walk right now.

278
00:26:02,555 --> 00:26:04,755
I could have made time
to take you to the hospital.

279
00:26:04,920 --> 00:26:07,400
He arranged for Ms. Dong,
the caregiver, to take me.

280
00:26:08,488 --> 00:26:10,000
Ms. Dong does this professionally.

281
00:26:10,000 --> 00:26:11,400
She's very familiar with the hospital.

282
00:26:11,422 --> 00:26:12,266
Where's my dad?

283
00:26:13,200 --> 00:26:15,000
What do you mean by Ms. Dong taking you?

284
00:26:15,270 --> 00:26:16,440
So he didn't even go himself?

285
00:26:16,920 --> 00:26:18,070
Why would he go?

286
00:26:18,960 --> 00:26:20,480
So he didn't let you tell me,

287
00:26:20,577 --> 00:26:22,088
and he didn't go himself either?

288
00:26:22,160 --> 00:26:24,830
He kept calling Ms. Dong
to ask about the situation.

289
00:26:27,440 --> 00:26:29,640
The out-of-pocket hospital expenses,

290
00:26:30,030 --> 00:26:31,070
and Ms. Dong's fees,

291
00:26:31,160 --> 00:26:32,200
he paid for all of it.

292
00:26:33,110 --> 00:26:34,640
You can't really say he doesn't care.

293
00:26:35,110 --> 00:26:37,510
Look at all this food.

294
00:26:37,680 --> 00:26:39,666
It's all what he told Ms. Dong to buy.

295
00:26:40,510 --> 00:26:42,160
If I hadn't taken this fall,

296
00:26:42,880 --> 00:26:43,880
I wouldn't have known

297
00:26:43,920 --> 00:26:45,933
he's actually attentive
when taking care of someone.

298
00:26:46,350 --> 00:26:47,480
What kind of care is that?

299
00:26:48,177 --> 00:26:50,110
Throwing some money
and making a few calls,

300
00:26:50,200 --> 00:26:51,400
and that counts as care?

301
00:26:51,720 --> 00:26:53,270
And those calls weren't even to you

302
00:26:53,550 --> 00:26:54,720
but to Ms. Dong.

303
00:26:56,310 --> 00:26:57,750
He told Ms. Dong as well.

304
00:26:58,377 --> 00:27:00,955
He said coming here himself
wouldn't be of any use.

305
00:27:01,422 --> 00:27:02,400
Ms. Dong also advised me.

306
00:27:02,800 --> 00:27:03,955
After thinking about it,

307
00:27:04,160 --> 00:27:04,680
she's right.

308
00:27:06,640 --> 00:27:07,920
Why did you come so early today?

309
00:27:11,510 --> 00:27:12,160
Well,

310
00:27:13,000 --> 00:27:13,640
I just

311
00:27:13,920 --> 00:27:15,030
worked through the night.

312
00:27:15,880 --> 00:27:17,240
I thought at this time

313
00:27:17,240 --> 00:27:18,850
you'd be up already,
so I came to see you.

314
00:27:18,911 --> 00:27:20,488
Who knew something
this serious happened,

315
00:27:20,533 --> 00:27:22,030
and you didn't tell me?

316
00:27:25,640 --> 00:27:27,270
Have you seen He Han lately?

317
00:27:28,350 --> 00:27:30,200
What's going on between you two?

318
00:27:33,400 --> 00:27:34,750
We're just like that.

319
00:27:35,550 --> 00:27:37,200
I don't agree with your dad.

320
00:27:37,720 --> 00:27:39,200
He only thinks highly of He Han

321
00:27:39,288 --> 00:27:40,920
and doesn't consider your happiness.

322
00:27:41,310 --> 00:27:43,270
I'm thinking from your perspective.

323
00:27:44,480 --> 00:27:46,110
If you can find someone suitable

324
00:27:46,310 --> 00:27:47,110
who treats you well,

325
00:27:47,911 --> 00:27:49,688
then don't keep holding on to He Han.

326
00:27:50,270 --> 00:27:51,880
Time matters to everyone.

327
00:27:53,550 --> 00:27:55,510
Don't end up like me,

328
00:27:56,022 --> 00:27:58,222
spending a lifetime holding on
to someone like air,

329
00:27:59,640 --> 00:28:01,440
neither far nor near,

330
00:28:01,920 --> 00:28:03,160
just living like this forever.

331
00:28:06,030 --> 00:28:07,030
That won't happen.

332
00:28:08,400 --> 00:28:09,640
The life you had with my dad,

333
00:28:09,640 --> 00:28:11,270
I couldn't endure
even a single day of it.

334
00:28:13,510 --> 00:28:15,160
Alright, you didn't sleep all night.

335
00:28:15,355 --> 00:28:16,400
Go back and get some rest.

336
00:28:16,790 --> 00:28:17,590
I'm doing fine here.

337
00:28:17,622 --> 00:28:18,800
What does that mean?

338
00:28:19,355 --> 00:28:20,800
You're driving me away now?

339
00:28:21,550 --> 00:28:24,240
Don't you usually like
to pull me into long chats?

340
00:28:24,240 --> 00:28:25,550
Before, I could move around,

341
00:28:25,550 --> 00:28:26,750
so I could take care of you,

342
00:28:27,110 --> 00:28:29,720
go to your place,
and cook and clean up for you.

343
00:28:30,510 --> 00:28:31,680
I can't even move now,

344
00:28:31,680 --> 00:28:33,111
so what's there to talk about?

345
00:28:33,955 --> 00:28:35,755
When you have time, go visit your dad.

346
00:28:35,830 --> 00:28:36,720
After this fall,

347
00:28:36,800 --> 00:28:38,000
I can't go see him anymore.

348
00:28:40,440 --> 00:28:42,066
I'll go speak with Ms. Dong for a bit.

349
00:28:42,350 --> 00:28:43,244
You rest for a while.

350
00:28:52,030 --> 00:28:52,550
Ms. Dong,

351
00:28:53,088 --> 00:28:54,755
thank you for taking care of my mom.

352
00:28:55,830 --> 00:28:57,270
Could you show me

353
00:28:57,310 --> 00:28:59,960
the contract between you and my mom
or between you and my dad?

354
00:29:00,088 --> 00:29:02,480
You know, elderly people
don't pay attention to these things.

355
00:29:02,550 --> 00:29:03,960
I have it, Miss Lin.

356
00:29:04,270 --> 00:29:05,160
The contract

357
00:29:05,350 --> 00:29:06,550
and my caregiving certificate,

358
00:29:06,590 --> 00:29:07,300
I have them all.

359
00:29:07,510 --> 00:29:07,880
Look.

360
00:29:09,400 --> 00:29:10,920
Our care center

361
00:29:10,920 --> 00:29:13,000
is very well known here in Shanghai.

362
00:29:13,160 --> 00:29:14,480
When your father came to us,

363
00:29:14,590 --> 00:29:16,480
he said he chose this place

364
00:29:16,480 --> 00:29:17,800
because of our high standards.

365
00:29:18,440 --> 00:29:20,830
But your father is particular.

366
00:29:21,480 --> 00:29:23,310
He went through quite a few people

367
00:29:23,590 --> 00:29:25,590
before finally choosing me.

368
00:29:25,800 --> 00:29:27,200
You're saying my dad is very picky

369
00:29:27,440 --> 00:29:28,880
and went through several people?

370
00:29:29,000 --> 00:29:29,640
Yes.

371
00:29:30,160 --> 00:29:32,070
He first came to
our company to look at profiles

372
00:29:32,070 --> 00:29:33,350
and then shortlisted a few.

373
00:29:33,480 --> 00:29:34,310
After that, he came,

374
00:29:34,310 --> 00:29:36,000
added each of us on WeChat,

375
00:29:36,160 --> 00:29:37,830
and questioned us one by one,

376
00:29:38,270 --> 00:29:39,790
like we were taking an exam.

377
00:29:39,960 --> 00:29:41,790
After rounds of screening,
it came down to

378
00:29:41,790 --> 00:29:43,270
another woman, surnamed Zou, and me.

379
00:29:43,377 --> 00:29:44,790
Then, he came to the company again,

380
00:29:44,790 --> 00:29:46,440
specifically to interview the two of us.

381
00:29:46,790 --> 00:29:49,790
He talked with me
for over an hour before deciding.

382
00:29:50,400 --> 00:29:51,270
Let me show you.

383
00:29:51,444 --> 00:29:52,911
These are the messages he sent me.

384
00:29:53,620 --> 00:29:54,430
(Do you have experience caring
for patients with limited mobility?)

385
00:29:54,430 --> 00:29:55,360
(Alright, could you
describe your wife's condition?)

386
00:29:55,360 --> 00:29:56,350
(She recently injured her back
in a fall. Needs round-the-clock care.)

387
00:29:56,350 --> 00:29:57,600
(I do have experience caring
for patients with back injuries)

388
00:29:57,610 --> 00:29:58,660
(Could you explain in detail
how you care for patients like this?)

389
00:29:58,680 --> 00:29:59,960
He was probably

390
00:30:01,110 --> 00:30:02,030
also at home

391
00:30:02,200 --> 00:30:04,160
looking up how to
treat your mom's condition.

392
00:30:05,240 --> 00:30:05,590
Look,

393
00:30:05,750 --> 00:30:06,830
he even sent me screenshots.

394
00:30:08,488 --> 00:30:10,000
He even copied down so much information.

395
00:30:11,222 --> 00:30:12,790
He really put a lot of thought into it.

396
00:30:12,790 --> 00:30:14,660
(She tends to overexert herself.
Make sure she doesn't get too tired.)

397
00:30:14,660 --> 00:30:15,540
(I bought moxibustion supplies.
Please apply it for 15 minutes daily.)

398
00:30:36,100 --> 00:30:39,540
(Shanghai Chenxing
Culture Media Co., Ltd.)

399
00:30:40,480 --> 00:30:40,830
Zhangzhu.

400
00:30:43,680 --> 00:30:44,110
What is it?

401
00:30:44,400 --> 00:30:45,400
I need to talk to you.

402
00:30:47,960 --> 00:30:48,510
Good morning.

403
00:30:48,960 --> 00:30:49,400
Morning.

404
00:30:50,550 --> 00:30:51,110
What is it?

405
00:30:51,830 --> 00:30:52,920
Do you have the draft

406
00:30:53,110 --> 00:30:54,111
He Han wrote for me?

407
00:30:54,177 --> 00:30:54,830
What do you want?

408
00:30:54,840 --> 00:30:55,733
I want to take a look.

409
00:30:56,333 --> 00:30:58,355
Ms. Lin said I'm not
allowed to show it to you.

410
00:30:58,510 --> 00:30:59,400
I won't tell her.

411
00:30:59,920 --> 00:31:00,790
I just want to know

412
00:31:00,790 --> 00:31:02,466
how he would write the same content.

413
00:31:03,466 --> 00:31:05,720
So you do have it, and you've read it?

414
00:31:06,111 --> 00:31:07,911
What would it take
for you to let me see it?

415
00:31:09,777 --> 00:31:11,640
To be honest,
I really want to send it to you,

416
00:31:11,688 --> 00:31:12,790
because once you read it,

417
00:31:12,790 --> 00:31:14,070
you'll understand how good he is.

418
00:31:14,080 --> 00:31:15,390
You're saying
he writes better than I do?

419
00:31:15,400 --> 00:31:15,880
Of course.

420
00:31:16,350 --> 00:31:17,480
Because you're his fan.

421
00:31:17,511 --> 00:31:18,960
I'm not the only one who's read it.

422
00:31:19,480 --> 00:31:20,920
Anyone who has read it knows.

423
00:31:21,750 --> 00:31:22,777
I don't believe it.

424
00:31:23,044 --> 00:31:24,640
If He Han really wrote it better,

425
00:31:24,660 --> 00:31:26,440
Lin Zhanqiao wouldn't have
sent out my version.

426
00:31:26,450 --> 00:31:28,490
I think Ms. Lin was just
trying to save your face.

427
00:31:28,640 --> 00:31:30,350
If she had thought
your writing was better,

428
00:31:30,590 --> 00:31:32,480
when I asked her why she sent yours

429
00:31:32,480 --> 00:31:34,000
instead of He Han's,

430
00:31:34,066 --> 00:31:35,110
she could have just said

431
00:31:35,110 --> 00:31:36,444
it's because yours was better,

432
00:31:36,488 --> 00:31:38,822
instead of saying, after all,
you're the original author.

433
00:31:43,422 --> 00:31:44,590
I'll go ask He Han for it.

434
00:31:44,720 --> 00:31:45,070
No.

435
00:31:45,070 --> 00:31:46,333
I want to learn from him.

436
00:31:46,733 --> 00:31:48,740
If you go to him directly,
Ms. Lin will be upset.

437
00:31:49,000 --> 00:31:49,640
You've already

438
00:31:49,640 --> 00:31:50,680
caused her so much trouble.

439
00:31:50,680 --> 00:31:52,030
You'd better not upset her again.

440
00:31:55,070 --> 00:31:56,110
Besides, I promised Ms. Lin

441
00:31:56,110 --> 00:31:57,270
I wouldn't say a single word.

442
00:32:04,940 --> 00:32:07,900
(Zhao Lanxin: Chapter 215
Drunk Old Friend: Hidden Depths.pdf)

443
00:32:10,130 --> 00:32:11,244
Alright. I won't make

444
00:32:11,500 --> 00:32:12,510
things difficult for you.

445
00:32:12,510 --> 00:32:13,688
Just pretend I never asked.

446
00:32:33,940 --> 00:32:38,220
(Chapter 215
Drunk Old Friend: Hidden Depths)

447
00:32:40,270 --> 00:32:41,790
How did you get He Han's draft?

448
00:32:42,088 --> 00:32:43,844
Don't we have someone on the inside?

449
00:32:43,911 --> 00:32:45,933
She's not in charge
of Gu Yan's manuscript, right?

450
00:32:46,022 --> 00:32:47,240
Well, He Han writes so well

451
00:32:47,250 --> 00:32:49,270
that people can't help
but share it with colleagues

452
00:32:49,270 --> 00:32:50,777
so that they can enjoy it, too.

453
00:33:01,488 --> 00:33:03,044
How did Gu Yan react after reading it?

454
00:33:03,400 --> 00:33:03,880
Two ways.

455
00:33:04,177 --> 00:33:05,440
Either he keeps it to himself

456
00:33:05,750 --> 00:33:06,590
and suffers silently,

457
00:33:07,350 --> 00:33:08,550
or he goes to Lin Zhanqiao

458
00:33:08,550 --> 00:33:10,350
to vent his jealousy and frustration.

459
00:33:10,750 --> 00:33:11,750
Definitely the first one.

460
00:33:12,400 --> 00:33:13,400
In this situation,

461
00:33:13,550 --> 00:33:15,750
he wouldn't dare show
any attitude to Lin Zhanqiao.

462
00:33:15,750 --> 00:33:17,720
That would be like
overturning his own table.

463
00:33:18,933 --> 00:33:20,400
For now, on Lin Zhanqiao's side,

464
00:33:20,400 --> 00:33:22,120
there's no one reliable
she can use either.

465
00:33:22,270 --> 00:33:23,377
It's a matter of leverage,

466
00:33:23,680 --> 00:33:24,790
seeing who needs whom more.

467
00:33:33,240 --> 00:33:34,222
You should understand.

468
00:33:34,400 --> 00:33:35,200
Sometimes this kind

469
00:33:35,200 --> 00:33:37,030
of walking-on-a-tightrope relationship

470
00:33:37,440 --> 00:33:39,350
ends up being
the most long-lasting and steady.

471
00:33:40,350 --> 00:33:41,240
It's a dynamic balance.

472
00:33:42,800 --> 00:33:44,830
But no matter how you put it,
walking a tightrope

473
00:33:45,200 --> 00:33:47,000
isn't exactly
something you'd call stable.

474
00:33:49,000 --> 00:33:50,640
No matter which of the two situations

475
00:33:50,640 --> 00:33:51,990
I just mentioned applies to Gu Yan,

476
00:33:52,030 --> 00:33:52,960
he will come to me.

477
00:33:53,720 --> 00:33:55,480
He wants Lin Zhanqiao
to be his safety net.

478
00:33:55,555 --> 00:33:57,000
But that net was woven for He Han,

479
00:33:57,000 --> 00:33:57,720
not for him.

480
00:33:58,160 --> 00:34:00,160
Mine is tailored just for him.

481
00:34:01,000 --> 00:34:02,270
You really haven't had it easy.

482
00:34:02,355 --> 00:34:03,880
You've made safety nets for everyone,

483
00:34:03,920 --> 00:34:05,240
pulling them in one by one.

484
00:34:05,733 --> 00:34:06,440
What about yours?

485
00:34:06,480 --> 00:34:07,160
Where is yours?

486
00:34:08,150 --> 00:34:08,840
I don't need one.

487
00:34:09,440 --> 00:34:10,440
Either I have everything,

488
00:34:10,630 --> 00:34:11,670
or I break completely.

489
00:34:16,688 --> 00:34:18,088
I have two pieces of good news.

490
00:34:18,550 --> 00:34:18,920
First,

491
00:34:19,440 --> 00:34:20,480
the new author we signed

492
00:34:20,480 --> 00:34:22,790
has entered the top ten of
the Newcomer Hundred-Day Ranking.

493
00:34:23,030 --> 00:34:23,440
Second,

494
00:34:23,977 --> 00:34:24,920
my parents hope we can

495
00:34:24,920 --> 00:34:26,933
get married
during the National Day holiday.

496
00:34:27,622 --> 00:34:29,360
The game room will be
under renovation then,

497
00:34:29,360 --> 00:34:30,190
so they'll be free.

498
00:34:30,622 --> 00:34:32,030
Your grandmother also hopes

499
00:34:32,030 --> 00:34:33,222
we can hold the wedding soon.

500
00:34:34,555 --> 00:34:35,600
National Day?

501
00:34:37,320 --> 00:34:38,670
There are too many weddings then.

502
00:34:38,670 --> 00:34:40,177
You won't be able to book a hotel.

503
00:34:40,200 --> 00:34:41,400
There wasn't one at first,

504
00:34:41,630 --> 00:34:43,630
but a couple canceled their reservation,

505
00:34:43,800 --> 00:34:44,480
about ten tables.

506
00:34:44,490 --> 00:34:45,870
Taking it over works perfectly for us.

507
00:34:45,880 --> 00:34:46,670
Seriously?

508
00:34:46,960 --> 00:34:49,070
Canceling a wedding banquet
just like that?

509
00:34:49,320 --> 00:34:50,630
The bride cheated and got caught.

510
00:34:50,666 --> 00:34:51,800
So, the wedding fell through.

511
00:34:51,840 --> 00:34:53,150
That's unlucky.
No, that won't do.

512
00:34:53,177 --> 00:34:54,133
I don't believe in that.

513
00:34:56,444 --> 00:34:57,880
Anyway, National Day is too rushed.

514
00:34:57,880 --> 00:34:59,511
A lot of things aren't prepared yet.

515
00:35:00,230 --> 00:35:02,440
Prepared or not,

516
00:35:02,760 --> 00:35:03,955
once the banquet is done,

517
00:35:04,360 --> 00:35:04,960
that's enough.

518
00:35:05,320 --> 00:35:07,422
What we want is the outcome,
not the process.

519
00:35:07,480 --> 00:35:09,733
Do you remember
what your friends' weddings were like?

520
00:35:10,022 --> 00:35:11,088
You don't, right?

521
00:35:11,177 --> 00:35:12,480
But once they've had the banquet,

522
00:35:12,480 --> 00:35:13,630
you know they're married.

523
00:35:13,630 --> 00:35:14,440
That's enough.

524
00:35:15,266 --> 00:35:16,590
If you think it's too much trouble,

525
00:35:16,590 --> 00:35:17,710
just leave everything to me.

526
00:35:17,800 --> 00:35:19,511
You just need to show up on time.

527
00:35:27,140 --> 00:35:28,900
(Hello. Due to health reasons,
updates will be paused for one week.)

528
00:35:28,920 --> 00:35:30,440
"Due to health reasons,

529
00:35:30,440 --> 00:35:32,377
updates will be
paused for a week." Why...

530
00:35:32,550 --> 00:35:33,670
Why is it so sudden?

531
00:35:33,760 --> 00:35:34,320
No idea.

532
00:35:36,840 --> 00:35:37,320
Zhangzhu,

533
00:35:37,800 --> 00:35:38,920
what's going on with He Han?

534
00:35:38,920 --> 00:35:40,440
Why did he suddenly stop updating again?

535
00:35:40,466 --> 00:35:41,777
Did he say anything to you readers?

536
00:35:41,960 --> 00:35:43,590
No. Everyone in the group is confused.

537
00:35:44,422 --> 00:35:45,377
Good morning, Ms. Lin.

538
00:35:46,360 --> 00:35:46,760
Ms. Lin.

539
00:35:50,333 --> 00:35:51,230
Morning, Ms. Lin.

540
00:35:51,288 --> 00:35:52,444
- Morning.
- Morning, Ms. Lin.

541
00:35:55,320 --> 00:35:56,070
Does Ms. Lin know?

542
00:35:57,670 --> 00:35:58,280
I'll go ask.

543
00:36:13,070 --> 00:36:14,840
Ms. Lin, you don't look too well.

544
00:36:17,710 --> 00:36:18,190
I'm fine.

545
00:36:19,280 --> 00:36:20,150
I didn't sleep well.

546
00:36:23,110 --> 00:36:23,800
What is it?

547
00:36:26,070 --> 00:36:28,000
Mr. He Han suddenly stopped updating.

548
00:36:28,800 --> 00:36:30,110
Ms. Lin, do you know why?

549
00:36:35,280 --> 00:36:36,000
Not really.

550
00:36:38,670 --> 00:36:39,440
After work,

551
00:36:39,840 --> 00:36:41,230
you can worry about He Han.

552
00:36:43,110 --> 00:36:44,400
Right now, go tell Mantou

553
00:36:44,760 --> 00:36:46,230
to call Mr. Fan immediately.

554
00:36:47,070 --> 00:36:48,510
While He Han is on hiatus,

555
00:36:49,190 --> 00:36:50,230
I want

556
00:36:50,590 --> 00:36:51,840
more exposure for Gu Yan.

557
00:36:58,533 --> 00:36:59,311
Cai Zhangzhu.

558
00:37:01,320 --> 00:37:01,880
Alright.

559
00:37:01,880 --> 00:37:02,790
I understand, Ms. Lin.

560
00:37:03,440 --> 00:37:04,030
Also,

561
00:37:04,880 --> 00:37:06,710
since He Han said
it's due to health issues,

562
00:37:07,440 --> 00:37:08,670
let him rest properly.

563
00:37:09,320 --> 00:37:10,960
A week will pass quickly.

564
00:37:13,488 --> 00:37:14,622
One more thing.

565
00:37:17,630 --> 00:37:19,320
I've read your apology letter.

566
00:37:21,320 --> 00:37:22,190
The same mistake

567
00:37:22,440 --> 00:37:24,400
must not happen again.

568
00:37:24,710 --> 00:37:25,070
Got it.

569
00:37:26,888 --> 00:37:28,377
Where have you been staying lately?

570
00:37:29,960 --> 00:37:31,190
A hotel near the company.

571
00:37:33,333 --> 00:37:34,355
Check out of the room.

572
00:37:34,920 --> 00:37:35,977
Move back and stay here.

573
00:37:38,710 --> 00:37:39,480
Thank you, Ms. Lin.

574
00:37:41,511 --> 00:37:42,440
I'll get back to work.

575
00:37:47,700 --> 00:37:52,220
(Meal)

576
00:38:02,190 --> 00:38:02,880
You're awake?

577
00:38:04,670 --> 00:38:05,880
I got you something to eat.

578
00:38:06,360 --> 00:38:07,440
Get up and have a bite.

579
00:38:12,070 --> 00:38:13,480
I've already informed Dingqi

580
00:38:14,444 --> 00:38:16,000
that you'll pause updates for a week.

581
00:38:16,480 --> 00:38:17,760
Take a good rest.

582
00:38:24,666 --> 00:38:26,330
Lie down a bit more.
I'll head out first.

583
00:38:27,550 --> 00:38:28,000
Dai Shan,

584
00:38:32,190 --> 00:38:33,190
help me find someone.

585
00:38:35,590 --> 00:38:36,280
Who?

586
00:38:37,840 --> 00:38:38,670
Xu Fenglian.

587
00:38:41,000 --> 00:38:41,480
My mom.

588
00:38:54,590 --> 00:38:55,150
Cai Zhangzhu?

589
00:38:55,920 --> 00:38:57,480
You came to see He Han?

590
00:38:59,110 --> 00:39:00,280
I came to ask

591
00:39:00,280 --> 00:39:01,550
how he is doing.

592
00:39:01,920 --> 00:39:02,960
Did Lin Zhanqiao send you?

593
00:39:03,400 --> 00:39:03,760
No.

594
00:39:05,150 --> 00:39:07,960
I'm here on behalf of the readers.

595
00:39:08,200 --> 00:39:09,280
He got a viral infection.

596
00:39:09,360 --> 00:39:10,440
He'll be fine in a week.

597
00:39:11,000 --> 00:39:12,840
But it's not
convenient for you to go in.

598
00:39:14,360 --> 00:39:15,190
A viral infection?

599
00:39:16,710 --> 00:39:18,360
But why aren't you wearing a mask?

600
00:39:18,590 --> 00:39:19,440
I just recovered.

601
00:39:19,622 --> 00:39:21,155
I'm still within the immunity period.

602
00:39:21,622 --> 00:39:23,000
You should head back first.

603
00:39:28,110 --> 00:39:28,480
Alright.

604
00:39:57,020 --> 00:40:00,540
(Cai Zhangzhu: Mr. He Han,
we're waiting for your update.)

605
00:40:00,540 --> 00:40:01,755
(Get well soon.)

606
00:40:14,800 --> 00:40:15,230
Ms. Lin.

607
00:40:18,550 --> 00:40:20,550
If there's nothing urgent,

608
00:40:20,577 --> 00:40:21,840
let's talk about it tomorrow.

609
00:40:22,280 --> 00:40:23,030
It's urgent.

610
00:40:25,880 --> 00:40:26,480
What is it?

611
00:40:26,577 --> 00:40:28,890
After the news of He Han
pausing updates for a week got out,

612
00:40:28,920 --> 00:40:29,920
just like last time,

613
00:40:30,030 --> 00:40:32,133
everyone is rushing
to contact Dingqi Platform.

614
00:40:34,190 --> 00:40:36,150
They want to take
this opportunity to stand out.

615
00:40:37,488 --> 00:40:38,400
That's normal.

616
00:40:38,630 --> 00:40:40,800
So I told you to contact
Mr. Fan as soon as possible

617
00:40:41,360 --> 00:40:43,230
to get more promotion for Gu Yan.

618
00:40:43,480 --> 00:40:44,110
I contacted him,

619
00:40:44,230 --> 00:40:45,920
but he said this situation is special.

620
00:40:46,288 --> 00:40:48,360
The platform has
already arranged a major move.

621
00:40:48,511 --> 00:40:49,466
It goes live tomorrow.

622
00:40:49,630 --> 00:40:50,440
What major move?

623
00:40:50,780 --> 00:40:52,288
The platform is keeping it confidential.

624
00:40:54,480 --> 00:40:55,590
It's going live tomorrow?

625
00:40:56,400 --> 00:40:58,280
They must have been
preparing it for a while.

626
00:40:58,320 --> 00:41:00,133
There's no way
there were no signs at all.

627
00:41:00,155 --> 00:41:01,511
I heard one possibility.

628
00:41:01,800 --> 00:41:02,190
What?

629
00:41:03,000 --> 00:41:04,480
The return of the Phantom Knight.

630
00:41:09,760 --> 00:41:10,280
Impossible.

631
00:41:13,000 --> 00:41:13,630
You actually

632
00:41:14,150 --> 00:41:15,230
came to me on your own?

633
00:41:17,440 --> 00:41:18,800
About the Phantom Knight,

634
00:41:19,280 --> 00:41:20,030
is it real?

635
00:41:21,000 --> 00:41:22,400
Real and fake.

636
00:41:25,110 --> 00:41:25,880
A fake?

637
00:41:26,280 --> 00:41:26,960
No.

638
00:41:27,400 --> 00:41:28,880
We don't do that kind of thing.

639
00:41:31,880 --> 00:41:33,710
Where would a Phantom Knight come from?

640
00:41:34,688 --> 00:41:36,280
He's been gone for so many years.

641
00:41:36,280 --> 00:41:38,360
No one even knows who he is.

642
00:41:38,710 --> 00:41:39,800
Who could find him?

643
00:41:39,880 --> 00:41:40,933
Even if you did find him,

644
00:41:41,230 --> 00:41:43,670
how could you be sure it's really him?

645
00:41:43,760 --> 00:41:45,230
The Phantom Knight can't be found.

646
00:41:45,710 --> 00:41:46,670
No one can find him.

647
00:41:47,550 --> 00:41:51,440
But I found his editor from back then.

648
00:41:52,422 --> 00:41:53,670
That editor is overseas now,

649
00:41:53,840 --> 00:41:54,880
working as a translator.

650
00:41:56,760 --> 00:41:58,070
As far as I know,

651
00:41:58,110 --> 00:42:01,230
even the editor
didn't know who Phantom Knight was.

652
00:42:01,230 --> 00:42:02,590
Back then,

653
00:42:02,590 --> 00:42:04,110
they communicated entirely by email.

654
00:42:04,480 --> 00:42:05,550
And the payments

655
00:42:05,760 --> 00:42:07,590
were all made
to an intermediary account.

656
00:42:08,360 --> 00:42:09,590
I don't care about all that.

657
00:42:10,150 --> 00:42:11,550
I found out about this

658
00:42:11,920 --> 00:42:13,280
around a month ago.

659
00:42:14,360 --> 00:42:15,920
That editor

660
00:42:16,480 --> 00:42:17,670
actually has

661
00:42:18,510 --> 00:42:19,670
the rights

662
00:42:20,070 --> 00:42:22,280
to an unfinished novel
by Phantom Knight.

663
00:42:25,000 --> 00:42:26,670
Unfinished?

664
00:42:26,955 --> 00:42:28,150
How much was completed?

665
00:42:28,840 --> 00:42:30,150
About a hundred thousand words.

666
00:42:30,360 --> 00:42:31,110
Fan,

667
00:42:31,110 --> 00:42:32,960
how much did you pay for that?

668
00:42:33,320 --> 00:42:34,110
A lot.

669
00:42:38,440 --> 00:42:39,590
Even if Mr. Fan could

670
00:42:39,590 --> 00:42:41,440
dig deep and track down Phantom Knight,

671
00:42:42,280 --> 00:42:44,030
after so many years away from it,

672
00:42:44,177 --> 00:42:46,155
he might not be
as good as he used to be.

673
00:42:46,510 --> 00:42:47,110
No matter what,

674
00:42:47,110 --> 00:42:49,360
Phantom Knight
is a legend among legends.

675
00:42:49,630 --> 00:42:50,400
If he appears,

676
00:42:50,400 --> 00:42:51,670
he'll overshadow everyone.

677
00:42:52,630 --> 00:42:53,577
I don't believe it.

678
00:42:53,777 --> 00:42:55,190
It goes live tomorrow, doesn't it?

679
00:42:55,960 --> 00:42:57,320
We'll respond accordingly.

680
00:43:05,921 --> 00:43:07,041
(I've been thinking.)

681
00:43:08,321 --> 00:43:11,601
(Everyone's most comfortable level of intimacy)

682
00:43:12,361 --> 00:43:19,691
(is probably different.)

683
00:43:20,691 --> 00:43:22,441
♪If the sky♪

684
00:43:22,951 --> 00:43:24,351
♪And the sea♪

685
00:43:24,891 --> 00:43:26,601
♪Turned upside down♪

686
00:43:28,161 --> 00:43:30,091
♪If a swimming fish♪

687
00:43:30,491 --> 00:43:33,881
♪Fell in love with a flying bird♪

688
00:43:35,651 --> 00:43:37,621
♪If back then♪

689
00:43:37,981 --> 00:43:42,391
♪We had never let go♪

690
00:43:42,991 --> 00:43:49,271
♪We wouldn't be lost in the crowd♪

691
00:43:50,391 --> 00:43:52,541
♪We met in a thirteenth month♪

692
00:43:52,541 --> 00:43:54,411
♪Held each other in a fifth season♪

693
00:43:54,591 --> 00:43:57,031
♪And found our way back whole♪

694
00:43:57,871 --> 00:44:00,041
♪So let this surging love♪

695
00:44:00,041 --> 00:44:04,471
♪Rise like tides that never fall♪

696
00:44:05,371 --> 00:44:07,551
♪If we're caught in a pouring rain♪

697
00:44:07,551 --> 00:44:08,641
♪That's alright♪

698
00:44:09,181 --> 00:44:09,931
♪If we're buried♪

699
00:44:09,931 --> 00:44:12,631
♪By passing years all the better♪

700
00:44:12,891 --> 00:44:15,071
♪At least we still can keep♪

701
00:44:15,251 --> 00:44:19,671
♪This one eternal photograph♪

702
00:44:35,431 --> 00:44:37,721
♪We're on misaligned tracks♪

703
00:44:37,721 --> 00:44:39,481
♪Running in opposite ways♪

704
00:44:39,601 --> 00:44:42,071
♪Searching all along the way♪

705
00:44:42,871 --> 00:44:45,031
♪For the fire of our younger hearts♪

706
00:44:45,221 --> 00:44:50,131
♪And the beauty lost in time♪

707
00:44:50,131 --> 00:44:53,651
♪This time don't lose each other again♪

708
00:44:53,891 --> 00:44:54,861
♪Only after loss♪

709
00:44:54,861 --> 00:44:57,491
♪Do we learn what truly matters most♪

710
00:44:57,901 --> 00:45:00,261
♪In another time and space♪

711
00:45:00,261 --> 00:45:01,821
♪We'll stay and walk together♪

712
00:45:01,821 --> 00:45:04,651
♪Till we grow old♪

713
00:45:05,611 --> 00:45:07,901
♪But still the sky will never♪

714
00:45:07,901 --> 00:45:10,571
♪Turn with the sea♪

715
00:45:13,091 --> 00:45:15,501
♪But still a swimming fish won't♪

716
00:45:15,501 --> 00:45:20,711
♪Fall in love with a flying bird♪
